<h1 style="margin:0 0 5px 0;">Update phpWCMS</h1>
<h3 style="margin:0 0 5px 0;">how to update correctly</h3>

</div><div style="margin:25px 0 0 0;padding:0;" class="spaceBeforeCP"></div>If you want to update a phpWCMS installation please follow these instructions. <br /><br />Save all your data wich you had changed. <br />Normaly these are the files and folders: <br /><br />
<DIV class=kasten>include/inc_conf/conf.inc.php<br />include/inc_conf/conf.template_default.inc.php<br />include/inc_conf/conf.indexpage.inc.php (seit 1.1-RC4 28.08.2004) template/inc_default/startup.html<br />template/inc_css/frontend.css<br />template/inc_cntpart<br /></DIV><HR>Now you unzip the new version of phpWMCS. <br /><br />It is encouraged to replace the new dates with your modified dates which you had backuped of the old version of phpWCMS. <br /><br />If you have installed an older version of phpWCMS ( for example RC2 ) <STRONG>edit the ( include/inc_conf/) manually</STRONG>. <br /><br />
<DIV class=kasten>include/inc_conf/conf.inc.php<br />include/inc_conf/conf.template_default.inc.php<br />include/inc_conf/conf.indexpage.inc.php (seit 1.1-RC4 28.08.2004) template/inc_default/startup.html<br />template/inc_css/frontend.css<br />template/inc_cntpart</DIV><br />
<HR>
<br />In the course of constant updating, the following data were continuously changed and developed further. <STRONG>Please</STRONG> <STRONG><FONT color=#ff0000>compare</FONT></STRONG> the data with data such as <STRONG>conf.template_default.inc.php, frontend.css</STRONG>. since new entries have been made.<br /><br />
<HR>
<br /><STRONG><EM><FONT color=#cc0033>TIP:</FONT></EM></STRONG><br />For the optimal comparison of two data we recommend the freewware-tool Winmerge. A special feature of this tool allows for the mating of two data, thus providing an optimal alignment of the text.&nbsp;<br /><br /><a href="http://winmerge.sourceforge.net/" target="_blank" class="phpwcmsExtLink">Here is the download</a><HR>Now upload the unzipped and edited new version and overwrite the existing phpWCMS installation.<HR>Now backup the database. If you haven’t done this yet, or you don’t know how to create a backup of your database, follow this link.

<ul class="articleLinkInternal">

	<li><a href="aid=196.phtml">Database Backup<img src="picture/myRT1/devR.gif" border="0" alt="" /></a></li>

</ul>

<br />If you have done this yet, just go ahead with reading.<HR><div class="imgDIVinTextLeft" align="left"><div class="image_td"><a href="zoom/N2FlOWZjOTdmNjRiNDhlYmMzMmM5NDZmZjVlOGZhMjEucG5nP3dpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjI3Ig.html" onclick="checkClickZoom();clickZoom('zoom/N2FlOWZjOTdmNjRiNDhlYmMzMmM5NDZmZjVlOGZhMjEucG5nP3dpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjI3Ig.html','previewpic','width.html');return false;.html"><img src="content/images/0a8083b208c01b247cb9eeee2438aa5e.png" width="150" height="117" border="0" class="image_img" alt="upgrade1.png" /></a></div><p class="image_caption">klick, to enlarge</p></div><div class="articleText"><P>Now we get to the actual updateprocess. For that, please go to <STRONG>upgrade.php</STRONG>. <br />You find this page in the setup folder of your phpWMCS installation. <br />(http://www.your_domain.com/setup/updgrade.php or http://www.your_domain.com/subfolder/setup/upgrade.php) <br /><br />When you open <STRONG>upgrade.php</STRONG>, you see this overview (picture on the left) <br /><br />in the upper part you see following fields: <br /><br /><STRONG>db host:</STRONG> your database host ( mostly Localhost) <br /><br /><STRONG>db name:</STRONG> your databasename <br /><br /><STRONG>db user:</STRONG> your database username <br /><br /><STRONG>db prepend: <br /></STRONG><br />select sql file: here you choose the SQL file which you want to update.</P></div><div style="margin:20px 0 0 0;padding:0;" class="spaceBeforeCP"></div><div class="imgDIVinTextLeft" align="left"><div class="image_td"><img src="content/images/1556880242b636ae68869177a7580c1f.png" width="150" height="111" border="0" class="image_img" alt="upgrade2.png" /></div></div><div class="articleText"><table height="134" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="70%" border="0">
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td>Now press the selectfield <strong>select sql file</strong> <br/>
            <br/>
            Now you see following variety: <br/>
            <br/>
            <strong>phpwcms_1.1-RC4_31-05-2004.sql <br/>
            phpwcms_1.1-RC4_25-08-2004.sql <br/>
            phpwcms_1.1-RC4_22-04-2004.sql <br/>
            phpwcms_update_older.sql <br/>
            phpwcms_1.1-RC4_13-08-2004.sql <br/>
            phpwcms_1.1-RC4_08-06-2004.sql</strong> </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table>
<br/>
<br/>
From the list, select first data after the installation release. In this case it would be the <strong>phpwcms_1.1-RC4_13-08-2004</strong>. <br/>
<br/>
If you have installed an older version, the data of the SQL files start with <strong>phpwcms_update_older.sql</strong>.</div><div style="margin:20px 0 0 0;padding:0;" class="spaceBeforeCP"></div><div class="imgDIVinTextLeft" align="left"><div class="image_td"><a href="zoom/MTc3NDE0N2NhNjMzMDRkODFjYWQwNjZmZDJjY2ZmYjcucG5nP3dpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjI3Ig.html" onclick="checkClickZoom();clickZoom('zoom/MTc3NDE0N2NhNjMzMDRkODFjYWQwNjZmZDJjY2ZmYjcucG5nP3dpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNjI3Ig.html','previewpic','width.html');return false;.html"><img src="content/images/0a8b9ac18b746b484d4db76c280eb01d.png" width="150" height="117" border="0" class="image_img" alt="upgrade3.png" /></a></div></div><div class="articleText"><table height="140" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="70%" border="0">
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td valign="top">Now you see in the textbox entries which will change. <br/>
            Now press <strong>Start upgrade</strong> to accept the innovations. <br/>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table></div><div style="margin:20px 0 0 0;padding:0;" class="spaceBeforeCP"></div><div class="imgDIVinTextLeft" align="left"><div class="image_td"><a href="zoom/OWU1N2JhMTQ4MmJlZmRjMDQzYzVkYTc2N2M1MjdiZjUucG5nP3dpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNTk3Ig.html" onclick="checkClickZoom();clickZoom('zoom/OWU1N2JhMTQ4MmJlZmRjMDQzYzVkYTc2N2M1MjdiZjUucG5nP3dpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNTk3Ig.html','previewpic','width.html');return false;.html"><img src="content/images/810f90e971a56b586752a0bd39c97a77.png" width="150" height="111" border="0" class="image_img" alt="upgrade4.png" /></a></div></div><div class="articleText"><table height="134" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="70%" border="0">
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td valign="top">After you execute the update of the database, you see an overview of the update. <br/>
            <br/>
            To make futher updates, click on <strong>Choose</strong> <strong>another SQL file</strong>. Then you get back to the startpage of the updatefunction. From there you can, if necessary and available, go on as described to install these. </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table></div><div style="margin:20px 0 0 0;padding:0;" class="spaceBeforeCP"></div><div class="imgDIVinTextLeft" align="left"><div class="image_td"><a href="zoom/OTM1ZTI3NmU4MjAwOTk5N2JlZDM1NTJjNjRhNzBlZTUucG5nP3dpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNTk3Ig.html" onclick="checkClickZoom();clickZoom('zoom/OTM1ZTI3NmU4MjAwOTk5N2JlZDM1NTJjNjRhNzBlZTUucG5nP3dpZHRoPSI4MDAiIGhlaWdodD0iNTk3Ig.html','previewpic','width.html');return false;.html"><img src="content/images/a8e003cb08677469d08cd11b378c9228.png" width="150" height="111" border="0" class="image_img" alt="upgrade5.png" /></a></div></div><div class="articleText"><table height="134" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="70%" border="0">
    <tbody>
        <tr>
            <td valign="top">
            <p align="justify">If you see this error, you probably have the current version of phpWCMS for which no updates are required or you have chosen an incorrect SQL-file. <br/>
            <br/>
            Please click again <strong>on another SQL file</strong> to select the next update, if available.&nbsp;<br/>
            </p>
            </td>
        </tr>
    </tbody>
</table></div>
